# AI Usage Tracking & Credits System — Walkthrough

## Overview

Implemented a full credits and usage tracking system for the foxmayn_ai platform. Organizations now have a credits balance (1 credit = 1 USD) that is consumed by AI operations (chat, embedding/indexing). Every AI API call is logged with token counts and cost for analytics.

## Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Client Request] --> B{creditsProcedure}
    B -->|No credits| C[402 Insufficient Credits]
    B -->|Has credits| D[Route Handler]
    D --> E[RAG Service]
    E --> F["OpenRouterQuery / OpenRouterEmbed"]
    F --> G["Returns {text/embeddings, usage}"]
    G --> H["logUsageAndDeduct()"]
    H --> I[ai_usage_log INSERT]
    H --> J["Atomic: org.credits_balance -= cost"]
    H --> K[credit_transaction INSERT]
```

---

## Changes Made

### Layer 1: Database Schema

#### [NEW] [usage/schema.ts](file:///home/nas/personal_projects/foxmayn_ai/packages/db/src/models/usage/schema.ts)
Two new tables with indexes and relations:
- **`ai_usage_log`** — every AI API call (org, user, model, tokens, cost, operation type)
- **`credit_transaction`** — audit trail for balance changes (topup/usage/refund/adjustment)

#### [NEW] [usage/types.ts](file:///home/nas/personal_projects/foxmayn_ai/packages/db/src/models/usage/types.ts)
Drizzle-zod inferred types.

#### [MODIFY] [auth/schema.ts](file:///home/nas/personal_projects/foxmayn_ai/packages/db/src/models/auth/schema.ts)
Added `creditsBalance` (real, default 0) to `organization` table.

